The paper deals with deep convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and their inference procedure for visual recognition tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of feedback-based propagation approach, which falls under the category of machine learning and optimization. Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the second most likely category. The paper also proposes an inference procedure that can be used for various visual recognition tasks, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the evaluation of various CNN architectures, which falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper also discusses the evaluation of the proposed approach on multiple simultaneous predictions, which falls under the category of natural language processing (cs.CL).
